description:
lib.rs:423-430 — algorithm_label has a _ => "unknown" catch-all:

    fn algorithm_label(algo: SigningAlgorithm) -> &'static str {
        match algo {
            SigningAlgorithm::EcdsaP256Sha256 => "ecdsa-p256",
            SigningAlgorithm::RsaPss2048Sha256 => "rsa-pss-2048",
            SigningAlgorithm::Ed25519 => "ed25519",
            _ => "unknown",
        }
    }

The catch-all is required because SigningAlgorithm is #[non_exhaustive]. But "unknown" discards the Debug-printable variant name, making the resulting AlgorithmMismatch error less actionable.

Suggested rewrite — change the return type to Cow<'static, str> (or String) and use Debug in the fallback:

    fn algorithm_label(algo: SigningAlgorithm) -> Cow<'static, str> {
        match algo {
            SigningAlgorithm::EcdsaP256Sha256 => "ecdsa-p256".into(),
            SigningAlgorithm::RsaPss2048Sha256 => "rsa-pss-2048".into(),
            SigningAlgorithm::Ed25519 => "ed25519".into(),
            other => format!("{other:?}").into(),
        }
    }

This requires AlgorithmMismatch.expected to accept a non-static string, which may be a core change. Alternative: just use format!("{algo:?}") directly at the call site instead of algorithm_label.
